  <span id="freeText5286460120580933492" style="display:none">I do think that every book has it’s place on a bookshelf somewhere with someone, how ever I am not that someone for this book. Initially I was intrigued with the Spanish text mixed in, however after a chapter or two it really became more frustrating to stop and look up the words my very limited knowledge of Spanish could not figure out.<br /><br /> The flow of this story is also very choppy. You begin a chapter thinking the story is going in one direction, however a detail is added or a character is introduced and then suddenly you have derailed and have no idea what is happening. If there were subtle connections between these transitions, I was not able to grasp them. </span>
